Question: How do I apply for accommodation on campus?
Answer: Hi there, I'm here to help with any student inquiries about university services. To apply for on-campus hostel accommodation, you can follow these steps:

Firstly, head over to the Student Portal and log in using your existing credentials. Once you're logged in, look for the "Hostel Accommodation" section.

Under this section, you'll find two main options: "Apply for Hostel Accommodation" and "View Available Hostels". To apply for hostel accommodation, click on the first option, which will take you to a page where you can select your preferred hostel block by uploading your proof of payment. Make sure to pay the non-refundable application fee before proceeding.

Please note that applications open online one month before the semester starts and are usually available until two weeks before classes commence. After submitting your application, results will be published on the portal.

If you need any further assistance or have questions about hostel accommodation, feel free to reach out to me via email at support@university.edu for guidance.
