A: On-campus hostel accommodation is allocated on a first-come, first-served basis, with priority given to first-year undergraduate and international students. Applications open online on the Student Portal one month before the semester starts. You must pay a non-refundable application fee first, select your preferred hostel block, and upload your proof of payment. Results are published on the portal two weeks before classes commence.

[FAQ - FEE PAYMENT]
Q: What are the rules and options for fee payment?
A: Tuition and hostel fees must be paid to the university bank accounts listed on the portal. Payments can be made via bank deposit, online bank transfer, or portal card payment. The university offers a two-installment plan: 60% must be paid prior to registration in week 1, and the remaining 40% must be paid by the 8th week of the semester. Students with outstanding balances will be blocked from accessing examination halls and receiving exam results.

[Ict Policies - Portal Access]
Portal Access
- URL: https://portal.udsm.ac.tz
- Services: Course registration, fee checking, exam results, hostel application
- Password reset: Via ICT Help Desk or self-service security questions

[Hostel Guidelines - Hostel Blocks]
Hostel Blocks
- **Hall 1** (Mlimani): First-year students, 4-person rooms
- **Hall 2** (Nkrumah): Second-year students, 2-person rooms  
- **Hall 3** (Nyerere): Senior students, single and 2-person rooms
- **Hall 4** (Kambarage): Postgraduate students, single rooms
- **Hall 5** (UDSM Tower): International students, single rooms with en-suite

[Hostel Guidelines - Application Process]
Application Process
1. Applications open online on the Student Portal one month before semester start
2. Pay non-refundable application fee of Tsh 20,000
3. Select preferred hostel block and room type
4. Upload proof of payment
5. Results published 2 weeks before classes commence
6. Accepted studen

