Official UDSM information:
[FAQ - EXAMINATION RULES]
Q: What are the rules regarding examinations and grading?
A: 1. Students must bring their valid Student ID card to all exam rooms.
2. No mobile phones, smartwatches, or unauthorized materials are allowed inside the exam hall. Possession of such items is treated as academic dishonesty.
3. Students arriving more than 30 minutes late will not be admitted.
4. Grading is based on a letter grade system (A to F). A GPA of 2.0 or above is required to remain in good academic standing. Supplementary examinations are held for students who failed with an 'F' grade but obtained a minimum GPA threshold of 1.5 in the semester.

[Examination Rules - Missed Examinations]
Missed Examinations
- Illness: Submit medical certificate within 7 days
- Bereavement: Submit death certificate and letter from parents
- Special exam will be arranged for approved cases
- Unexcused absence: Grade F automatically

[Library Services - Fines]
Fines
- Overdue books: Tsh 500 per book per day
- Lost books: Replacement cost + Tsh 20,000 processing fee
- Damaged books: 50% of replacement cost
- Unpaid fines: Blocked from borrowing, exam results withheld

[Ict Policies - Portal Access]
Portal Access
- URL: https://portal.udsm.ac.tz
- Services: Course registration, fee checking, exam results, hostel application
- Password reset: Via ICT Help Desk or self-service security questions

