[FAQ - FEE PAYMENT]
Q: What are the rules and options for fee payment?
A: Tuition and hostel fees must be paid to the university bank accounts listed on the portal. Payments can be made via bank deposit, online bank transfer, or portal card payment. The university offers a two-installment plan: 60% must be paid prior to registration in week 1, and the remaining 40% must be paid by the 8th week of the semester. Students with outstanding balances will be blocked from accessing examination halls and receiving exam results.

[Registration Procedures - New Student Registration]
New Student Registration
1. Check admission status on the student portal
2. Accept admission offer online within 2 weeks
3. Pay acceptance fee of Tsh 50,000
4. Upload required documents: 
   - Birth certificate
   - Academic certificates (secondary school, diploma, etc.)
   - Passport-sized photographs (2)
   - Medical clearance report
5. Receive student registration number
6. Pay tuition fees (first installment minimum 60%)
7. Register for courses online via student portal
8. Attend orientation week

[Graduation Requirements - Undergraduate Programmes]
Undergraduate Programmes
- Complete minimum of 120 credit units (3-year programme) or 160 credit units (4-year programme)
- Achieve minimum CGPA of 2.0
- Complete all compulsory/core courses for the programme
- Complete internship/industrial attachment (minimum 8 weeks)
- Complete final year research project/dissertation
- No outstanding fees or library obligations
- No pending disciplinary cases

[Fee Structure - Tuition Fees per Semester]
Tuition Fees per Semester
- Bachelor of Arts: Tsh 1,200,000
- Bachelor of Science: Tsh 1,500,000
- Bachelor of Engineering: Tsh 2,000,000
- Bachelor of Law: Tsh 1,800,000
- Bachelor of Commerce: Tsh 1,400,000
- Bachelor of ICT: Tsh 1,600,000
- Master's Programmes: Tsh 2,500,000 - 4,000,000
- PhD Programmes: Tsh 3,000,000 - 5,000,000

