Official UDSM information:
[FAQ - COURSE REGISTRATION]
Q: How do I register for courses?
A: Course registration is done online via the Student Portal during the first two weeks of the semester. To register: log in to your portal, navigate to 'Course Registration', select your required and elective courses based on your curriculum sheet, and click 'Submit'. You must consult your Academic Advisor before finalizing. The deadline for adding or dropping courses is the Friday of the second week of lectures.

[Ict Policies - Portal Access]
Portal Access
- URL: https://portal.udsm.ac.tz
- Services: Course registration, fee checking, exam results, hostel application
- Password reset: Via ICT Help Desk or self-service security questions

[Academic Regulations - Course Registration]
Course Registration
- Registration opens 2 weeks before semester start, closes end of Week 2
- Students must register for a minimum of 4 courses (12 credits) and maximum of 7 courses (21 credits) per semester
- Adding/dropping courses permitted during first 2 weeks of lectures
- Late registration incurs a penalty fee of Tsh 50,000
- All registrations must be approved by the Academic Advisor

[Academic Calendar - Semester 2 (February - June)]
Semester 2 (February - June)
- Course registration: February 2 - February 20
- Lectures begin: February 9
- Add/Drop deadline: February 20
- Mid-semester break: March 30 - April 5
- Continuous assessment tests: April 6 - April 17
- Study leave: May 25 - May 31
- Final examinations: June 1 - June 14
- Semester break: June 15 - August 31

